<treatment id="5DC89711AF075AC182850CF699211DA3" ID-GBIF-Taxon="194444363" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:5DC89711AF075AC182850CF699211DA3" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/5DC89711AF075AC182850CF699211DA3" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<subSubSection id="1E0BB5D7428E0A4EEC5C664A73E4BEE4" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="0CD1CCE0F277C649570AE61E7306CC82" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="DE164067C6251158B7FB7A0E423F05A5" LSID="5DC89711-AF07-5AC1-8285-0CF699211DA3" authority="(Gravenhorst, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Woldstedtius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Woldstedtius flavolineatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolineatus">Woldstedtius flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5C826CDB21BFB200672290F90CC8985" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7771F1C6BE1ECC3C0D2C896A3EF07BEF" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28E8F026DECF560E9A85E6801FAE8776" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
This species is divided into two subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="EEBEEECAD1E6764A8B7667383A214349" authority="flavolineatus" genus="W." lsidName="W. flavolineatus subsp. flavolineatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="subSpecies" species="flavolineatus" subSpecies="flavolineatus">
<emphasis id="37540AD027FC42A23EF134C399C3D383" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. flavolineatus flavolineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7BC2DA0B38FB65F7F51985DDE4D08689" genus="W." lsidName="W. f. subsp. nigroscutellatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="subSpecies" species="f." subSpecies="nigroscutellatus">
<emphasis id="3EA548F5D5D0FE29C5949115F0BFA870" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. f. nigroscutellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Habermehl, 1925). The latter subspecies has been recorded from Germany and Netherlands (
<bibRefCitation id="824F8AF8A24F44FEC4EBB5D4A1D6755C" author="Habermehl, H" journalOrPublisher="Konowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="264 - 276" refId="B10" refString="Habermehl, H, 1925. Beitraege zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Ichneumonidenfauna. Konowia 4: 264 - 276" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Ichneumonidenfauna." volume="4" year="1925">Habermehl 1925</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0CB7A0D691B899FF5B7255F879353AF9" author="Teunissen, HGM" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="10 - 38" refId="B20" refString="Teunissen, HGM, 1948. Naamlijst van inlandse sluipwespen (Fam. Ichneumonidae I). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 89: 10 - 38" title="Naamlijst van inlandse sluipwespen (Fam. Ichneumonidae I)." volume="89" year="1948">Teunissen 1948</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="A5A151ACBCF70EC6B93EEBE9CE5AE6D0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3801.1.1" author="Klopfstein, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 143" refId="B13" refString="Klopfstein, S, 2014. Revision of the Western Palaearctic Diplazontinae (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). Zootaxa 3801 (1): 1 - 143, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3801.1.1" title="Revision of the Western Palaearctic Diplazontinae (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3801.1.1" volume="3801" year="2014">Klopfstein (2014)</bibRefCitation>
noted this subspecies could not be examined by her because type specimens were not available. Judging from the original description of the latter (
<bibRefCitation id="181409F680FBC326E70A438612CC1615" author="Habermehl, H" journalOrPublisher="Konowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="264 - 276" refId="B10" refString="Habermehl, H, 1925. Beitraege zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Ichneumonidenfauna. Konowia 4: 264 - 276" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Ichneumonidenfauna." volume="4" year="1925">Habermehl 1925</bibRefCitation>
), this subspecies could readily be synonymized under the former.
</paragraph>
